<paragraph blockId="14.[151,549,258,280]" box="[151,549,258,280]" pageId="14" pageNumber="487">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1914" box="[151,362,259,280]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Makilingia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis box="[151,362,259,280]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="487">Makilingia maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 1914: 412, 
<figureCitation box="[489,549,258,280]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,960,982]" captionTargetBox="[334,1225,296,910]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[324,1263,265,939]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. A, Makilingia xanthopicta n. sp., male genital capsule, lateral view, with parts labeled. B–F, Makilingia suturalis Melichar, holotype (drawings by D. A. Young): B, head and pronotum, dorsal view, left side; C, male genital capsule, lateral view; D, left male subgenital plate, ventral view; F, aedeagus, lateral view; F, style and connective, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2627163/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="487">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,325,998]" pageId="14" pageNumber="487">Male genitalia. Pygofer appendage moderately broad, nearly straight, extended well beyond apex of lobe. Subgenital plate moderately long and robust, slightly but evenly curved dorsad, distal lobe lightly pigmented ventromedially, darkly pigmented dorsolaterally, dorsal callosity small. Style with preapical lobe forming right angle, apex footlike with angulate preapical heel. Aedeagus in lateral view with preatrium nearly as long as shaft, moderately broad and strongly curved; shaft broad, robust with weak anteroapical ridge; in posterior view with preatrium broad constricted medially, atrium with pair of large weakly bilobed lateral flanges, shaft broad basally, tapered distally to rounded apex.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,325,998]" pageId="14" pageNumber="487">Female. Sternite VII less than twice as wide as long, tapered, posterior margin with pair of narrow lateral lobes flanking broader, shorter medial lobe. Second valvula with dorsal margin biarcuate, teeth numerous, short, blunt.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
